	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>LSDJ on real MBC5 cartridge</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have the typical 64M EMS cartridge many people have, but it draws a lot of power and looks like it has neither current limiting resistors nor level shifting buffers between the 3.3V ROM, RAM, and CPLD on board and the cartridge slot (5V).<br /><br />I'm interested in taking a MBC5 game (one of the Legend of Zelda ones), removing the mask rom, and soldering a 29F**** series flash chip in place. Are there any reasons this shouldn't give me a proper dedicated LSDJ cartridge? I was thinking of buying the GB everdrive but it appears to not be properly compatible with LSDJ.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
